parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended lowering of the tailgate while driving can cause a loss of cargo or create a hazard on the road, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The tailgate lowers by itself while driving
even when the key fob is not in close proximity to the tailgate release button.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Loss of Power and Momentum
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and momentum can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic, as it can lead to a loss of control or collision with other vehicles.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power and momentum while driving
resulting in a sudden slowdown
often without warning or any diagnostic trouble codes. This can occur at various speeds
including highway and low-speed driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loss of Engine Power and Transmission Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of engine power and transmission issues can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when merging into traffic or navigating intersections.
symptoms: The engine loses power
the vehicle hesitates or stalls
the engine RPM remains at idle despite pressing the accelerator
the vehicle struggles to accelerate
the vehicle enters a "limp mode" without warning lights or codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning backup camera can cause the driver to lose visibility while reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The backup camera remains on while driving forward
obstructing the driver's view.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the tailgate latch can cause the tailgate to fall off, potentially damaging the vehicle and posing a safety risk to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: The tailgate falls off while driving
the tailgate does not latch properly
the tailgate is loose or unstable
the tailgate makes a rattling or clunking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sudden Loss of Power and Acceleration
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power and acceleration can lead to a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks or hesitates
the check engine light comes on
the vehicle slows down or declines in acceleration
the engine RPMs increase but the vehicle speed does not
the vehicle struggles to maintain speed
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive wear on the front rotors can cause vibrations, affecting vehicle stability and control, which can lead to accidents. Insufficient rotor thickness can also compromise braking performance.
symptoms: Steering wheel shakes or vibrates
vehicle shakes or vibrates
uneven or excessive brake rotor wear
reduced braking performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rotors with insufficient thickness can compromise braking performance, leading to longer stopping distances and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Reduced braking performance
increased stopping distance
uneven or excessive brake rotor wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure by the service department to properly inspect and maintain the vehicle can lead to premature wear and compromise safety.
symptoms: Insufficient rotor thickness
uneven or excessive brake rotor wear
reduced braking performance
increased stopping distance.
